Defendant Pamela Shead in court with attorney Gary Edward Rosenthal.  David Robles appeared for the State of Wisconsin. State placed negotiations on the record. Court finds the state has complied with the victim rights legislation. Statements made as to sentencing.  

As to Count 1:  
Court ordered defendant to serve 10 DAYS in the House of Correction with credit for good time; straight time. Court will allow defendant to serve sentence on consecutive weekends if allowed by the sheriff's department. HUBER privileges for work will be allowed if defendant can provide proof of employment. Defendant must report by 11/6/2015 at 3:00 p.m.


As to Count 2:  
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 28 MONTHS; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 14 MONTHS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 14 MONTHS.  

Court STAYED the sentence on Count 2 and placed defendant on probation for 5 YEARS with the following conditions:

Conditions of Probation:
1) Restitution in the amount of $730.00 payable to Pamela B to be paid first;
2) Restitution in the amount of $19,830.21 to be paid second;
     $7,323.49 GE Capitol 
     $4,933.98 Comenity Bank
     $468.68    CitiBank
     $3,168.07 Chase Coldwater Creek
     $3,935.99 HSBC (Capitol One)
3) Pay all costs, fees, surcharges, and restitution. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
4) Provide DNA sample and pay DNA surcharge;
5) Defendant to enter into a payment plan with agent and pay no less than $100.00 per month towards costs, fees, surcharges & restitution;
6) No contact with Pamela B.;
7) Participate and provide proof of gambling therapy;
8) Participate in gamblers anonymous if the defendant discontinues therapy;
9) Provide proof to agent of at least 4 hours of credit counseling or financial counseling.

If revoked court costs, fees, surcharges and restitution be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds/wages.

